# Automerge Usage

## repo.find is async

`repo.find()` is async and always returns a valid handle — no need to null-check.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const handle = await repo.find(url);

// ❌ BAD
const handle = repo.find(url); // missing await
```

## Use repo.doc, not repo.docSync

`docSync` is deprecated. Always use the async `repo.doc`.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
const doc = await handle.doc();

// ❌ BAD
const doc = handle.docSync();
```

## Delete properties instead of assigning undefined

Automerge does not support `undefined` values. Delete the property instead.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
repo.change(handle, (doc) => { delete doc.foo; });

// ❌ BAD
repo.change(handle, (doc) => { doc.foo = undefined; });
```

## Assign clean objects, not automerge objects

Never reassign objects that came from an automerge document — they carry internal metadata. Spread or reconstruct a plain object first.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
doc.target = { x: other.x, y: other.y };

// ❌ BAD
doc.target = other; // other is an automerge proxy object
```
